@page "/admin/app-registry"
@model AppRegistryAdminModel

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Application Registry — Platform Admin";
}

<h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Application Registry Management</h1>

<p class="govuk-body">
    This page is for <strong>Platform Administrators</strong> only. It provides an overview of the
    Application Registry API and links to the interactive Swagger UI where you can execute
    management operations.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What is the Application Registry?</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
    The Application Registry is the authoritative store of client applications that integrate
    with the CDP platform. Each application record defines:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li><strong>Application</strong> — the client system (e.g. a procurement service or front-end portal).</li>
    <li><strong>Permissions</strong> — fine-grained capabilities that can be granted (e.g. <code>read:organisations</code>).</li>
    <li><strong>Roles</strong> — named collections of permissions assigned to users or service accounts.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Operational workflow</h2>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
    <li>
        <strong>Register the application</strong> — call <code>POST /api/applications</code> with the
        application name, description, and client ID. Note the returned <code>id</code> (the <em>appId</em>).
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Define permissions</strong> — call <code>POST /api/applications/{appId}/permissions</code>
        for each permission the application exposes.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Create roles</strong> — call <code>POST /api/applications/{appId}/roles</code> for each
        role (e.g. <em>Viewer</em>, <em>Editor</em>, <em>Admin</em>).
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Assign permissions to roles</strong> — call
        <code>PUT /api/applications/{appId}/roles/{roleId}/permissions</code> with the full list of
        permission IDs for each role.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Verify</strong> — call <code>GET /api/applications/{appId}/roles</code> to confirm
        permissions are correctly assigned.
    </li>
</ol>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
    All write operations (<code>POST</code>, <code>PUT</code>, <code>DELETE</code>) require a valid
    Platform Admin token obtained via the <code>client_credentials</code> OAuth 2.0 grant with the
    <code>platform_admin</code> scope. Read operations on individual resources do not require the
    Platform Admin scope.
</div>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">API reference</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
    The full interactive API documentation is available in the Swagger UI. You can use it to
    explore all endpoints and execute requests directly against the live service.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
    <a class="govuk-link" href="/swagger/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Open Organisation API Swagger UI (opens in a new tab)
    </a>
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
    Filter by the <strong>Application</strong> or <strong>Application - Permissions</strong> /
    <strong>Application - Roles</strong> tag groups to find the relevant endpoints. All Platform
    Admin-restricted endpoints are marked with the <em>[Platform Admin]</em> prefix in their summary.
</p>
